#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:9
msgid "SYNOPSIS : Installation of syslinux instead of grub"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:12
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"DESCRIPTION :\n"
" Syslinux is a small and fast bootloader.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:18
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"PRE-REQUISITIES :\n"
"A working LFS (tested with a LFS 7.0). \n"
"  It is useful to have a LFS with GRUB installed, which can already boot.\n"
"nasm (see BLFS)\n"
"python (see BLFS : python 2.7)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:20
msgid "HINT:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:23
msgid ""
"The purpose of this hint is to replace GRUB, in a working LFS, or install "
"Syslinux in a LFS you are building"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:27
msgid ""
"ATTENTION : the tricks of this hint will install a bootloader; these tricks "
"are potentially dangerous for your system. If there is a problem, the system "
"may not boot anymore."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:30
msgid ""
"Step 1 : Downloading the source and untar them You can download the source "
"at:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:32
msgid "http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/utils/boot/syslinux/syslinux-4.05.tar.xz"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:34
msgid "Next, you need to untar them"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:36
msgid "tar -xf syslinux-4.05.tar.xz"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:39
msgid ""
"The source also contains the binaries of the files. If desired, it is "
"possible to skip compilation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:41
msgid "Step 2 : Compilation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:43
msgid "The compilation is quite simple:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:45
msgid "make"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:47
msgid "Note: The compilation needs nasm and python ."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:49
msgid "Step 3 : Installation of the binaries"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:51
msgid "Using the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:53
msgid "make install"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:55
msgid "The \"syslinux\" installers are now installed on your LFS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:57
msgid "Step 4 : Booting with Syslinux"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:63
msgid ""
"Here is the interesting part of the hint. Note that this hint only deals "
"with using extlinux, which enables a system to boot from an ext2, ext3 or "
"ext4 partition. It is possible to use syslinux to boot from a CD, a FAT "
"disk, etc...  For more information about the other methods, see the official "
"website (www.syslinux.org)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:65
msgid "You need to create a directory to install the bootloader"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:67
msgid "mkdir /boot/extlinux"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:69
msgid "then use extlinux to install the bootloader"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:71
msgid "extlinux --install /boot/extlinux"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:73
msgid "Step 5 : Configuring"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:75
msgid "The configuration will be in a /boot/extlinux/syslinux.conf file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:77
msgid "In its shortest aspect, this file will contain:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:82
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"DEFAULT lfs\n"
"LABEL lfs\n"
"   KERNEL /boot/vmlinuz.img\n"
"   APPEND ro root=/dev/xxx\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:85
msgid ""
"vmlinuz.img : kernel image, or some symlink to the kernel image /dev/xxx : "
"partition which contains your system"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:89
msgid ""
"For more information about the configuration file, I suggest you to see the "
"documentation. It is possible to have a menu and choose what system you "
"would like to boot, boot in PXE, display a file, ..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:92
msgid ""
"You need to check that your partition is configured properly to boot (with "
"the boot flag)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:94
msgid "To set this flag:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:99
msgid ""
"fdisk /dev/yyy (with yyy the disk name e.g. sda, sdb, etc)  then, choice a "
"then give the partition number which should have the Boot flag.  Press w to "
"save"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:101
msgid "For example, to set the /dev/sda1 partition with the boot flag:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:106
msgid ""
"fdisk /dev/sda Command (m for help): a Partition number (1-4): 1 Command (m "
"for help): w"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:109
msgid ""
"Then, you need to set the mbr (it will replace the grub installation if it "
"has already been installed)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:111
msgid "In the source tree, change to the mbr directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:113
msgid "then run the command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:115
msgid "cat mbr > /dev/yyy (with yyy the boot disk name, e.g. sda, sdb ...)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:117
msgid "Step 6 : test"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:120
msgid ""
"Now the installation is completed, the system must be rebooted to check that "
"syslinux works properly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:124
msgid ""
"ATTENTION : You should create a rescue boot media for your system. If "
"syslinux has a problem, your system will not reboot. You should have a "
"liveCD, to rescue if you have a problem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:127
msgid ""
"Normally, with the minimal configuration file created above, your computer "
"should start directly on the LFS kernel."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/syslinuxen.txt:128
msgid "Syslinux is installed."
msgstr ""
